    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-04-30T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-04-30T10:00:00-05:00" n="712"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d712">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89 Czechoslovakia/43: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pearson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Prague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-04-30T16:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 30, 1923—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. Legation’s number 21, April 13, 3 p.m.<note n="14" xml:id="d712fn14">Not
                        printed.</note> Debt Commission sailing May 5 on <hi rend="italic"
                        >Berengaria</hi> from Cherbourg.<note n="15" xml:id="d712fn15">The
                        Commission was composed of Dr. Chvalkovsky, appointed Czechoslovak Minister
                        to the United States; Dr. Lipansky, Counselor of the Ministry of Finance;
                        Captain Křenek, of the Ministry of National Defense; and Francis Pisecky,
                        Director of the Corn Office.</note> Minister for Foreign <pb facs="0995"
                        n="879" xml:id="pg_879"/> Affairs informed me this morning Commission is
                    authorized to conduct negotiations for repayment but must refer any agreement
                    reached back to Czech Government for final approval.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Pearson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
